{
  "id": "S2P05K31",
  "title": {
    "product_var": "ZPRODTSK",
    "text": "KEY CATEGORIES",
    "version_var": "ZSHRTVER",
    "prefix": "HELP"
  },
  "type": "menu",
  "body": {
    "rows": [
      {
        "type": "command",
        "variable": "ZCMD"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "The MOUSE category allows assignments of the different mouse"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "events that may occur:  Left/Right click and Double Click."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Though any SPF command may be assigned to a mouse event,"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "(including END), the terminal functions [CURSOR-MOUSE] and"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "[CURSOR-MOUSE-SELECT] are the most appropriate."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Finally, the CUSTOM category lists just keys that are"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "customly assigned to your keyboard.  As some keyboards"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "have keys that are non-standard, these special keys"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "may be named and have SPF command and functions assigned to"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "them, just like any other key.  See CUSTOM KEY ASSIGNMENT"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "for more details."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
